trend_summary: From earliest to latest imagery, the planned suburban settlement roughly doubles its built footprint through infill housing, expanded town-center retail and widened arterial roads. Forest cover contracts, especially around the northern highway corridor, while the central golf course remains largely intact. Change is steady and incremental, reflecting moderate growth.
notable_changes: Progressive residential infill in curvilinear cul-de-sac neighborhoods encircling the golf course
New big-box and light-industrial roofs along the northern arterial, replacing woodland
Highway/interchange in southeast widened, with additional ramps and paved areas
Town-center block gains larger parking lots and retail footprints, reducing tree cover
Small agricultural/wooded patches on northeast edge converted to housing estates
